SOMATOTROPIN is a 4-element fingerprint that provides a signature for 
somatotropin, prolactin and related hormones. The fingerprint was derived
from an initial alignment of 12 sequences: the motifs were drawn from
short conserved regions spanning the C-terminal half of the alignment -
motif 1 spans helix 2, and includes the region encoded by PROSITE pattern
SOMATOTROPIN_1 (PS00266), which contains one of the Cys residues involved
in intramolecular disulphide bond formation; motif 2 spans helix 2, leading
into helix 3; motifs 3 and 4 span helix 6, and include the region encoded by
PROSITE pattern SOMATOTROPIN_2 (PS00338), which contains two other conserved 
Cys residues. Three iterations on OWL30.0 were required to reach convergence,
at which point a true set comprising 172 sequences was identified. Several
partial matches were also found, all of which are related sequences and
fragments that fail to match one or two motifs.

An update on SPTR37_9f identified a true set of 160 sequences, and 22
partial matches.
